item.title: Different servers
item.dc:creator: @glestrts glestrts
item.description:
@glestrts wrote:

[quote=“statsflamescape, post:1, topic:337584”]Can any 1 gme a list of different servers and there purpose
ex: 317 is a (put definition of server)?[/quote]
alright the numbers… are called revisions. basically every time jagex updated the client, the revision changed.

317 is the classic old school client in use atm, and in its pure state featured old falador, while having ancients which were ~300-311?

~400 new cache loading system.

~422 interface reworking,

~438 hunter added
459- greater old school feel, while having skillcapes and old school character models and gameframe.

474- godswords, godwars, new gameframe

484- has summoning and 474 char models, newer maps.

499- height of the runetek2 game engine, complete new maps, and newer chars on an old engine client.

503-554? runetek 3 (ld) and runetek4 (hd)

notable versions in this category include
~525 statius/ vesta
531-soul wars

555, glitchy version, runetek5 released
556-current runetek5.
